messages.message: Hey, work and life are great. Still doing QA as far as work goes, learning swift at night right now. Sami(who you need to meet at some point) and I have 2 dogs now which is a whole thing but wonderful. We are moving across town next month so we're looking at places right now. I'm playing in a band in Raleigh with some friends which is fun. Anyway definitely staying busy. How's stuff on your end?

Brian
Good. Swift is fun. The testing suite has some bugs though. Took a job at Charles Schwab. Working on a side project sosmethod.herokuapp.com

Access management for internal support. It is really boring. Corporate world moves a lot slower. People don't understand the purpose of educating others. I've heard "I don't want to distract people" from managers, as if they have the right to decide what is a distraction for me and I can't make that decision on my own. Fucking retarded.

Brian
Are you using swifts internal test suite or selenium or something else?
Sikuli is cross platform too.
I am writing a bot to fill out my time sheet from one source that has to match 2 other sources.
I have to record my time log in 3 places.

Unreal how silly things get in the world of big corporations but clearly your head is in the right place
I use selenium about 30 hrs a week at work
But with c#
Haven't done anything with sikuli
Are you doing that in swift?

Brian
Sikuli can do OS automation. So you could write a selenium script that makes a call to the sikuli web service that starts the iOS test script to interact in between selenium commands.

Oh sweet
I'm gonna have to dive in deeper on that

Brian
Yeah end to end integration testing. I am writing robots in selenium to automate checking accounts so I don't need an app for everything.
